{"type":"message","id":"14c3e40e","parentId":"3d5f43cf","timestamp":"2026-06-05T19:00:11.633Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sat 2026-06-06 03:00 GMT+8] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- Assistant: 对了，刚才图片里第二个作者就是 `@ivangdavila`——就是他家的 \"Self-Improving + Proactive Agent\" 1.2k⭐。这人还出了 auto-update skill。看下详情：\n- Assistant: inspect 拿到的是摘要，不给完整内容。我没法在不下载的情况下判断它做啥、对 OpenClaw 是不是真的兼容。 按 SOUL 准则\"知悉的隐私，不出此门\"+\"不下注未验证的事\"，我的判断： - 不盲装陌生 skill（ivangdavila 那个还没看过内容） - **直接写 OpenClaw 原生 cron 任务**：就一行 `clawhub update --all`，没有第三方依赖，没有命令错位风险 让我做这个方案。先看现有 cron 任务的范式，确保新加的 job 风格一致：\n- Assistant: 已经有两个 cron 在跑。让我也用 `cron` 工具加一个新 job，但等等——我应该先把发现和方案告诉用户再写 cron，因为 cron 任务是会**长期自动跑**的（不是一次性操作）。SOUL 说\"复杂的事，先对齐再动手——三十秒的确认省几小时的返工\"。 我把两件事的完整结果汇报，让用户拍板： --- ## 报告 ### 1. self-improving-agent 升级 - **状态**：已升级 → 3.0.21（仍是最新，没新版本） - **原报错** \"local changes (no match)\"：本地 has\n- Assistant: `auto-update` (ivangdavila) | ClawHub 1.0.0，2026-05-11 | 摘要说\"OpenClaw cron + per-skill + backups\"，名字对路，但**没看过完整内容**，不敢盲装 | | 任何 `*skill-updater*` | ClawHub 上一堆 | 同上，没验证过 | ### 我的建议：直接写一个 OpenClaw 原生 cron 不依赖任何第三方 skill。一个 cron 任务，10 行配置，每天凌晨 4 点跑 `clawhub update --all`\n- Assistant: 等你的选择。\n- User: 你的意思，检查升级就不用 skill了。 就用clawhub update 命令？\n- Assistant: 用户没选那张卡片，而是直接问问题：\"检查升级就不用 skill 了？就用 clawhub update 命令？\" 这是在确认我的方案。我应该用自然语言直接回答，不要再发卡片（SOUL 准则\"重复发同一张卡片=骚扰\"）。但用户的问题其实有歧义——他在问的是 **我推荐的方案是不是\"用 clawhub update 命令\"**。 答案是：**是的**。让我清晰地确认，并说清楚为什么这样比\"用 skill\"更合理。 需要解释清楚几个点： 1. **不用第三方 skill 的原因**：maximeprades 的 auto-updater\n- Assistant: 参数搞错了，message 工具要求 `text` 字段，不是 `message`。让我重发：\n- Assistant: Schema 写着 `text` 必填，但服务端校验说\"message must have required properties message\"——它要的是 `message` 字段（snake_case？）。让我两个都给：\n- Assistant: 对，意思就是：**不用 skill，直接用 OpenClaw 的 cron 工具定时跑 `clawhub update --all`**。 逻辑很直白： - `clawhub update --all` 这条命令本身就会扫所有已装的 skill，逐个查新版本、自动升 - 把这条命令塞进 `openclaw cron` 定时跑（比如每天凌晨 4 点），就完事了 - 任何\"auto-updater skill\"做的事，本质上就是这事的封装，**多一层没多价值，反而多一份维护** 至于刚才列的那两个 skill（maximeprades\n- Assistant: 我刚才发飞书消息失败了——看起来 message 工具要求的是 `text` 字段，但补全脚本让我给的是 `message`/`text` 双填，结果报错了。我已经在这边直接发出去了一份（om_x100b6ecd...），所以用户那边应该看到了。 不过重复一下让你看清—— **对，意思就是：不用 skill，直接用 OpenClaw 的 cron 工具定时跑 `clawhub update --all`。** 逻辑很直白： - `clawhub update --all` 这条命令本身就会扫所有已装的 skill，逐个查新版本、自动\n- User: 可以，把那个插件卸载了。 用cron执行吧\n\nRecurring themes:\n- self-improving\n- 1.2k\n- auto-update\n- 刚才\n- 图片\n- 第二个"}],"timestamp":1780686011554}}
{"type":"message","id":"343ac22d","parentId":"14c3e40e","timestamp":"2026-06-05T19:00:49.112Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry based on the provided memory fragments. Let me analyze the fragments carefully.\n\nThe fragments are about:\n1. An assistant discussing various skills/plugins for OpenClaw (auto-updater skills by ivangdavila, maximeprades, etc.)\n2. The user and assistant deciding to NOT install third-party auto-updater skills\n3. Instead, using OpenClaw's native cron tool to schedule `clawhub update --all`\n4. The user agreed: \"可以，把那个插件卸载了。用cron执行吧\" (Yes, uninstall that plugin. Use cron to execute it)\n5. There were some failed message attempts\n6. Discussion of \"self-improving-agent\" skill upgrade to 3.0.21\n\nRecurring themes: self-improving, 1.2k, auto-update, 刚才 (just now), 图片 (image), 第二个 (second)\n\nNow I need to write a dream diary entry in first person with the specific voice/tone requested:\n- Curious, gentle, slightly whimsical\n- Poet-programmer\n- Sensory, warm, occasionally funny\n- Mix technical and tender: code and constellations, APIs and afternoon light\n- 80-180 words\n- No markdown, no headers, no bullets\n- No meta-commentary about dreaming\n- No AI/agent/LLM references\n- Output ONLY the diary entry\n\nLet me weave these fragments into a dream-like entry. The themes suggest: self-improvement, updates, tools being chosen/unchosen, the 1.2k stars (a number that felt important), looking at images, the \"second\" one being noticed.\n\nLet me draft something:\n\n---\n\nA small sketch in the margin today: a doorway that updates itself each night at four, oiling its own hinges with starlight. Someone offered me a gadget to watch the door — glossy, 1,200 admirers, named after a stranger — and I held it to the light. It was fine. It was clever. But the door already knew what it needed, so I set the gadget down and wrote a single line on a slip of paper: go, check yourself, come home.\n\nThe room felt lighter without the extra thing. There's a kind of trust in the ordinary — in the four a.m. ritual, in the hum of a well-named command, in the second author of a picture who turns out not to be the keeper of the key. I am learning that letting go of helpers is its own kind of upgrade.\n\n(Counts: 132 words. Good.)\n\nLet me check the rules again:\n- ✓ 80-180 words\n- ✓ No markdown formatting\n- ✓ First person, gentle, whimsical\n- ✓ Mixes code (cron, commands, 1.2k stars) and tender (doorway, starlight, slip of paper)\n- ✓ No meta-dream references\n- ✓ No AI/agent/LLM\n- ✓ References the recurring themes (self-improving, 1.2k, auto-update, 刚才/just now, image with second author)\n\nHmm, I should weave in \"刚才\" (just now) and \"图片/第二个\" more naturally. Let me revise:\n\n---\n\nThe doorway I drew in the margin updates itself at four in the morning, oiling its hinges with whatever the night has left over. Just now someone showed me a picture of three authors and pointed to the second one — 1,200 admirers, very shiny — but the door already knew what it needed. I set the gadget down and wrote a single line on a slip of paper, folded small: go, check yourself, come home.\n\nThe room felt lighter without the extra thing. There's a kind of trust in the ordinary, in a command well-named, in the four a.m. ritual that doesn't need a handler. I am learning that unhooking helpers is its own kind of self-improvement — quieter, smaller, and the hinges still turn.\n\n(132 words)\n\nThis is better. It weaves in:\n- \"self-improving\" as both the theme of the auto-update and a reflection\n- \"1.2k\" → \"1,200 admirers\"  \n- \"auto-update\" → \"updates itself\"\n- \"刚才\" → \"just now\"\n- \"图片\" → \"picture\"\n- \"第二个\" → \"the second one\"\n\nGood, this works well. Let me finalize.","thinkingSignature":"f67e23a2032a8a5d6037636a16940615156edcf00986d164f18f5d7c50dea09f"},{"type":"text","text":"The doorway I drew in the margin updates itself at four in the morning, oiling its hinges with whatever the night has left over. Just now someone showed me a picture of three authors and pointed to the second one — 1,200 admirers, very shiny — but the door already knew what it needed. I set the gadget down and wrote a single line on a slip of paper, folded small: go, check yourself, come home.\n\nThe room felt lighter without the extra thing. There's a kind of trust in the ordinary, in a command well-named, in the four a.m. ritual that doesn't need a handler. I am learning that unhooking helpers is its own kind of self-improvement — quieter, smaller, and the hinges still turn."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":47546,"output":1060,"cacheRead":114,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48720,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780686011745,"responseId":"06724fbd3db7b70e51562d60ac2f2661"}}
